-- Stanbic Uganda Says Annual Profit Surged 69% on Loans
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-04-04T06:04:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/stanbic-uganda-says-annual-profit-surged-69-on-loans-1-.html
Stanbic Bank Uganda Ltd. (SBU) , the
nation’s biggest lender, said profit climbed 69 percent last
year after it boosted loans.  Net income rose to 121.7 billion shillings ($49 million)
from 72.1 billion shillings in 2010, the Kampala-based bank said
in a statement published in the New Vision newspaper today.  Loans and advances climbed 25 percent to 1.5 trillion
shillings last year, while interest accruing from loans to
customers advanced 68 percent to 266.7 billion shillings, the
bank said.  Retained earnings rose 41 percent to 293.5 billion
shillings, it said.  Stanbic Uganda is a unit of the South African-based
 Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK) ,  Africa ’s biggest lender.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
